  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bae\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1  \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Two years after the MCC rejected the agreement, the Cabinet approved an agreement to receive a grant from the United States.",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The cabinet has approved the idea of \u200b\u200breceiving a grant from the United States two years after the Gotabhaya Rajapakse government refused to accept $ 480 million under the US MCC agreement.",
        "Sri Lanka will receive $ 37 million through two agreements between the Sri Lankan and US governments.",
        "The two countries will sign an agreement on projects based on two objectives: strengthening cooperation for democratic good governance and social cohesion and building sustainable economic growth.",
        "The idea put forward by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe is to sign an agreement with the United States Agency for International Development to implement a $ 57 million funding program through the USAID.",
        "Named the 'Program for a Prosperous Democratic Prosperous Sri Lanka Until 2026', the program focuses on areas such as development, governance, secure market-based development and strengthening.",
        "In November 2021, President Rajapakse said after the visit of then Foreign Secretary Mike Pompeo that his government would never sign the mcc agreement proposed by the United States. However, a month after Rajapaksa's statement, the US canceled the concession to Sri Lanka."
      ],
